For backwards compatability, these constructors should remain the same and instead call a new constructor which has the label as the final parameter.
So instead of adding a label in all the constructors:
public Example(String example1, String Label, String example2) {
    this(example1, label, example2, null);
}

public Example(String example1, String Label, String example2, Integer example3) {
    // do stuff
}
Leave the constructors as they are so any existing code still call them and they maintain the same behaviour:
public Example(String example1, String example2) {
    this(example1, example2, null, null);
}

public Example(String example1, String example2, Integer example3) {
    this(example1, example2, example3, null);
}

// new constructor
public Example(String example1, String example2, Integer example3, String label) {
    // do stuff
}

